main event: A civilian observed a single unidentified object with red and white lights in Kensington, Maryland on February 20, 1967.
interesting points: The observer reported the object moving in a southwest direction,The observation lasted for about 10 minutes,The object was described as a light, not resembling a conventional aircraft,The shape was sketched as oval or egg-like,The witness has a background in astronomy and is considered an expert.
sighted object: a light with red and white colors
witness description: The witness is a 30-year-old female college graduate in astronomy considered an expert in her field.
